                        <th scope="row" class="display-5">Scott Pilgrim</th>
                        <td>Scott Pilgrim is the so called "protagonist" of the story. As it follows that he is an adult unwilling to grow up. He goes through struggles like responsibility or any trait that an adult carries. With this, he makes many mistakes unintentionally. We often forget or as the story sugar coats his mistakes percieving him as the "good guy" or the "victim". Though when we thoroughly analyze his character, he also has his faults and the unreliable narrator of the story. </td>
                        <td><img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/c8/ad/0e/c8ad0e11ab6398549674ca46878c1851.jpg" alt="Scott Pilgrim" width="250" height="250" class="img-thumbnail float-end"></td>
